Organizations can connect on-premises Active Directory with Microsoft Entra ID using synchronization tools like Azure AD Connect.

This enables:

* Hybrid identity
* Password hash sync
* Pass-through authentication

For example, employees use the same credentials for local and cloud resources.

A real-life use case is enterprises transitioning gradually to cloud identity.

Another example is maintaining legacy systems while adopting Microsoft 365.

Hybrid identity ensures consistency and smooth migration.
